[b]WaveTrend — Momentum Oscillator with Overextension Analysis[/b]

[b]What it does[/b]
WaveTrend measures how far price deviates from a smoothed equilibrium and compresses that deviation into an oscillator. Cross signals fire when the oscillator crosses its signal line, classified by zone (extreme, mid-negative, mid-positive) so you always know whether a cross is inside an oversold extreme or just a noise event in the middle of the range.

Three optional extensions sharpen the core:
[list]
[*][b]Extension A — Overextension Duration[/b]: counts consecutive bars inside the OB/OS zone. When that count exceeds your threshold, weak and regular crosses are suppressed — preventing whipsaw exits during a sustained trend. Strong crosses are never filtered.
[*][b]Extension B — Slope Quality Filter[/b]: measures the oscillator's rate of change. A flattening slope inside OB/OS signals exhaustion; a still-rising slope signals trend continuation. Slope context is shown on strong cross tooltips and in the dashboard.
[*][b]Extension C — Zone Persistence[/b]: tracks consecutive bars above or below zero. When the count reaches the configured minimum, the dashboard shows a "Sustained Bull/Bear" label — identifying wave-riding conditions where counter-trend signals should be discounted.
[/list]

[b]Cross Signals[/b]
[list]
[*][b]Strong ▲▼ (large)[/b] — cross inside an extreme zone; highest reversal probability
[*][b]Regular ▲▼ (medium)[/b] — cross in negative/positive but not extreme territory
[*][b]Weak ▲▼ (small)[/b] — cross on the same side as the current bias; continuation context
[/list]
Set "Cross Signals" to [i]Strong[/i] to see only actionable extremes, [i]All[/i] for every event, or [i]None[/i] to disable markers entirely.

[b]Divergence Detection[/b]
[list]
[*][b]Regular Bullish (RB)[/b] — price lower low, oscillator higher low → reversal potential
[*][b]Hidden Bullish (HB)[/b] — price higher low, oscillator lower low → trend continuation
[*][b]Regular Bearish (RS)[/b] — price higher high, oscillator lower high → reversal potential
[*][b]Hidden Bearish (HS)[/b] — price lower high, oscillator higher high → trend continuation
[/list]
Each divergence draws a line between pivot points and places a labelled marker at the current pivot.

[b]Compare Symbol[/b]
Enable to overlay WaveTrend for a second instrument (default: BINANCE:BTCUSDT) on the same chart. Divergences between two assets can reveal hidden strength or weakness in the primary symbol.

[b]Price-Chart Overlay[/b]
Projects the oscillator structure directly onto the price panel so you can read momentum without switching panes. Choose Top, Middle, or Bottom placement and adjust height and vertical offset. Three color themes: Default (teal/red/blue), Vibrant (neon), Monochrome (grayscale).

[b]Dashboard[/b]
Top-right panel showing: oscillator value, signal value, zone, momentum direction, latest cross state, divergence type, market regime, extreme warning, extension readings (duration, slope, sustained bias), and composite directional bias with confidence percentage.

